Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.740 --> 00:00:10.541
Hello, my names Professor Bruce Maycock.

00:00:10.541 --> 00:00:15.450
I'm the head of school of Public Health at
Curtin University and I'd like to welcome

00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:21.090
you to our school, to the university, and
if you are new, to Perth Western Australia.

00:00:21.090 --> 00:00:22.380
To the land of the Noongar people.

00:00:22.380 --> 00:00:26.590
If you're looking at this video you're probably
thinking about coming to Curtin University

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:28.240
to study Public Health.

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:32.920
By choosing to enrol at Curtin you've enrolled
in the only school of Public Health in Western

00:00:32.920 --> 00:00:33.920
Australia.

00:00:33.920 --> 00:00:37.100
We offer you a unique learning experience.

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:42.860
That will include high quality instruction,
skill development and the opportunity to apply

00:00:42.860 --> 00:00:45.510
that knowledge in different settings.

00:00:45.510 --> 00:00:52.299
Through initiatives such as Interprofessional
Education, Global Exchange, Professional Placement,

00:00:52.299 --> 00:00:56.450
and accredited programs we seek to produce
the best graduates in Australia.

00:00:56.450 --> 00:01:02.879
We offer undergraduate programs in Food Science,
Health Information Management, Health Promotion,

00:01:02.879 --> 00:01:07.030
Health Sciences, and Nutrition.

00:01:07.030 --> 00:01:13.649
Our postgraduate areas of study include our
flag ship higher degree program with PhD,

00:01:13.649 --> 00:01:18.259
Doctor of Public Health Programs and a Master
of Philosophy.

00:01:18.259 --> 00:01:21.909
We also have a well acknowledged Master of
Public Health Program.

00:01:21.909 --> 00:01:28.729
We have graduate certificates, postgraduate
diplomas, and masters programs in dietetics,

00:01:28.729 --> 00:01:35.149
environmental health, food science, health
information management, health policy and

00:01:35.149 --> 00:01:40.979
management, health promotion, occupational
health and safety, and sexology.

00:01:40.979 --> 00:01:46.560
The majority of our staff are active researchers,
and are able to bring to you the cutting edge

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:52.259
knowledge and experiences that you will require
upon graduation.

00:01:52.259 --> 00:01:56.579
One of the things that makes this a unique
school of Public Health is that our staff

00:01:56.579 --> 00:02:00.420
are still active in doing Public Health work.

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:06.990
Whether it be creating new and healthier food
products, conducting health and safety assessments,

00:02:06.990 --> 00:02:12.530
facilitating the development of international
policy or conducting laboratory or clinical

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:18.170
trials - our staff are still doing the research
and advocacy that is needed to improve the

00:02:18.170 --> 00:02:20.340
health of those in our region.

00:02:20.340 --> 00:02:24.110
It is the experience of the staff that will
make a difference.

00:02:24.110 --> 00:02:28.120
I really hope to see you soon, at Curtin,
in our school of Public Health.

